<p>Under the doctrine of <strong>RESPONDEAT SUPERIOR</strong> an employer, <strong>master</strong> or principal is<strong> vicariously liable</strong> for all torts committed by an employee, servant or agent, respectively, if the tort is committed within the <strong>scope of the employment</strong> or agency relationship.    </p>
<p>Respondeat superior <strong>does not apply</strong> to independent contractors.</p>
